body:
Hi there!

I encountered a segmentation fault when using an out-of-scope variable with some slicing.

Here is an example:

`tb.sv`:
```
module testbench;

  bit [31:0] first_words [64 / 32];
  bit [31:0] second_words [32 / 32];

  bit [63:0] first;
  bit [31:0] second;

  top dut(first, second);

  always_comb begin
    for (int first_word_id = 0; first_word_id < 64 / 32; first_word_id++) begin : reset_generator
      first_words[first_word_id] = first[32*first_word_id +: 32];
    end
    for (int second_word_id = 0; second_word_id < 32 / 32; second_word_id++) begin : reset_generator
      second_words[second_word_id] = second[32*first_word_id +: 32]; // Note the usage of first_word_id here
    end
  end

endmodule
```

`top.sv`:
```
module top(first, second);
  output [63:0] first;
  wire [63:0] first;
  output [31:0] second;
  wire [31:0] second;
endmodule
```

Command: `iverilog -g2012 -o out top.sv tb.sv`

Result:
```
tb.sv:16: error: Unable to bind wire/reg/memory `first_word_id' in `testbench.$ivl_for_loop1.reset_generator'
Segmentation fault
```

The bug is still present in the most recent version of Icarus (`c9548f0`), and I'm running on Ubuntu 22.04.

Thanks!
Flavien

